      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>white long grain rice </strong>to<strong> </strong>an <strong>oven-proof dish </strong>with<strong> </strong>a pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and 300ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[600ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong>, mix everything together and cover tightly with<strong> tin foil</strong></p><p>Once the duck legs have had an initial 30 min, remove them from the oven and spoon the duck fat all over, basting them twice more until golden and crispy</p><p>Return the<strong> </strong>duck legs with the rice to the oven for 30 min further or until all the water is absorbed and the rice is cooked – these are your <strong>roasted five-spice duck legs </strong>and<strong> baked rice</strong></p><p>Meanwhile, combine the <strong>honey</strong>, <strong>toasted sesame oil</strong>,<strong> half </strong>the <strong>ginger & garlic paste </strong>(you'll use the rest later!) and <strong>remaining cornflour</strong> in a bowl with 80ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[100ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> and a very generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> – this is your <strong>sesame-honey sauce</strong></p>",
